Praggnanandhaa R (2690) - Carlsen, Magnus (2835)
FIDE World Cup (chess24.com) [65] 2023.08.22
A29 English, four knights, kingside fianchetto

1.c4 e5 2.Nc3 Nf6 3.Nf3 Nc6 4.g3 d5 5.cxd5 Nxd5 6.Bg2 Nf6 7.b4 Bd6 8.b5 Nd4 9.Qa4 Nxf3+ 10.Bxf3 O-O 11.O-O a6 12.d3 h6 13.Ba3 Rb8 14.Bxd6 cxd6 15.Rab1 axb5 16.Qxb5 Bd7 17.Qb6 Bc6 18.Qxd8 Rfxd8 19.Bxc6 bxc6 20.Kg2 Ra8 21.Rb6 Rdc8 22.Rc1 d5 23.Rc2 Nd7 24.Rb1 Nc5 25.Rbc1 Ra5 26.Nb1 Ne6 27.Nd2 Rca8 28.Nf3 e4 29.dxe4 dxe4 30.Nd2 e3 31.Nc4 Rxa2 32.Nxe3 Nd4 33.Rxa2 Rxa2 34.Rc4 c5 35.Rxc5 Rxe2

00:00 Hello Everyone!

The Chess World Cup 2023 is a 206-player single-elimination chess tournament that will take place in Baku, Azerbaijan, from 30 July to 24 August 2023.[1] It will be the 10th edition of the Chess World Cup. The top three finishers in the tournament will qualify for the 2024 Candidates Tournament.[2][3]

The tournament will be held in parallel with the Women's Chess World Cup 2023.
